  "text": "The SESD needs to reach the bottom tree level immediately, in order to update the radius and perform tree pruning: the depth-first sequential order makes it hard to adopt parallel processing architectures. The resulting throughput is variable and tends to drop down significantly at low SNR region. Furthermore, the performance becomes much worse when the number of visited nodes is bounded with the purpose of reducing the detection complexity and latency in real applications [CITATION_1] . In order to obtain a constant throughput, a constant number of nodes must be visited. Sub-optimal detection methods have been",
